First Lady Michelle Obama has announced the opening of the Old Family Dining Room on the public tour route of the White House. The room has been refurbished and will showcase 20th-century art and design. The Old Family Dining Room has a rich history dating back to 1825. As part of the renovation, several artworks have been added to the permanent White House collection, including pieces by Alma Thomas, Robert Rauschenberg, Josef Albers, and Anni Albers. The room will reflect the history of former First Families and the legacy of modern American artists. Visitors can find additional information about tours of the White House on the official website.